The paper discusses model-based control and learning dynamics models for robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a novel online learning algorithm for correcting dynamics errors, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The approach is adaptive and involves real-time correction, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also involve computer vision techniques, as the robot's data stream may include visual information (cs.CV).
